 {"id":"rust_proxy-x3z","title":"Implement error suggestion system","description":"## Implement Error Suggestion System

### Overview

Create a system that generates actionable suggestions based on error types and context, helping users resolve issues without documentation lookup.

### Architecture

```rust
pub trait ErrorWithSuggestions {
    /// Get contextual suggestions for this error
    fn suggestions(&self) -> Vec<String>;
}

pub struct SuggestionEngine {
    /// Error pattern -> suggestions mapping
    patterns: Vec<SuggestionPattern>,
}

struct SuggestionPattern {
    /// What to match (error type, message patterns, etc.)
    matcher: Box<dyn Fn(&dyn std::error::Error) -> bool>,
    /// Suggestions to provide
    suggestions: Vec<String>,
}
```

### Suggestion Mappings

| Error Type | Pattern | Suggestions |
|------------|---------|-------------|
| ConnectionRefused | `kind == ConnectionRefused` | "Check that the proxy server is running", "Verify the proxy address and port are correct", "Check firewall rules allow outbound connections" |
| Timeout | `kind == TimedOut` | "Check network connectivity", "Increase timeout with --timeout flag", "Verify proxy server is responsive" |
| DNS Resolution | `contains("resolve")` | "Check the hostname is correct", "Verify DNS configuration", "Try using IP address instead" |
| Permission Denied | `kind == PermissionDenied` | "Run with sudo for system operations", "Check file ownership and permissions" |
| Config Parse Error | `is ConfigError::Parse` | "Check TOML syntax at the indicated line", "Verify all required fields are present", "Run 'rp check' for detailed validation" |
| Auth Required | `contains("407")` | "Configure proxy credentials in config file", "Check username/password are correct" |
| Port In Use | `contains("address already in use")` | "Check if another instance is running", "Use a different port with listen = \"127.0.0.1:PORT\"" |

### Implementation

```rust
impl SuggestionEngine {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        let mut patterns = Vec::new();

        // Connection refused
        patterns.push(SuggestionPattern {
            matcher: Box::new(|e| {
                e.to_string().to_lowercase().contains("connection refused")
            }),
            suggestions: vec![
                "Check that the proxy server is running".to_string(),
                "Verify the proxy address and port are correct".to_string(),
                "Check firewall rules allow outbound connections".to_string(),
            ],
        });

        // Timeout
        patterns.push(SuggestionPattern {
            matcher: Box::new(|e| {
                let s = e.to_string().to_lowercase();
                s.contains("timeout") || s.contains("timed out")
            }),
            suggestions: vec![
                "Check network connectivity to the proxy".to_string(),
                "Increase timeout in configuration".to_string(),
                "Verify proxy server is responsive".to_string(),
            ],
        });

        // DNS
        patterns.push(SuggestionPattern {
            matcher: Box::new(|e| {
                let s = e.to_string().to_lowercase();
                s.contains("resolve") || s.contains("dns") || s.contains("no such host")
            }),
            suggestions: vec![
                "Check the hostname is spelled correctly".to_string(),
                "Verify DNS configuration on this machine".to_string(),
                "Try using IP address instead of hostname".to_string(),
            ],
        });

        // Add more patterns...

        Self { patterns }
    }

    pub fn get_suggestions(&self, error: &dyn std::error::Error) -> Vec<String> {
        self.patterns
            .iter()
            .filter(|p| (p.matcher)(error))
            .flat_map(|p| p.suggestions.clone())
            .collect()
    }
}
```

### Formatting

```rust
pub fn format_error_with_suggestions(error: &dyn std::error::Error) -> String {
    let suggestions = SUGGESTION_ENGINE.get_suggestions(error);

    let mut output = format!("Error: {}\n", error);

    if !suggestions.is_empty() {
        output.push_str("\nSuggestions:\n");
        for (i, suggestion) in suggestions.iter().enumerate() {
            output.push_str(&format!("  {}. {}\n", i + 1, suggestion));
        }
    }

    output
}
```

